descp2: Diagonal offset(s). Positive value means superdiagonal, 0 refers to the main diagonal, and negative value means subdiagonals. `k` can be a single integer (for a single diagonal) or a pair of integers specifying the low and high ends of a matrix band. `k[0]` must not be larger than `k[1]`.

Diagonal offset(s). Positive value means superdiagonal, 0 refers to the main diagonal, and negative value means subdiagonals. `k` can be a single integer (for a single diagonal) or a pair of integers specifying the low and high ends of a matrix band. `k[0]` must not be larger than `k[1]`.
